File: The power utility stated they have been using their emergency resources to generate enough electricity for the country. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says it does not expect to implement load-shedding on Sunday. The power utility communicated it is using emergency electricity generation reserves to compensate for unplanned breakdowns on Saturday. Eskom reiterated that while no power cuts are expected, load-shedding could be implemented on short notice. READ: LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you The possibility of increased power cuts remains over the next 18 months as critical maintenance continues.